            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Like many Americans, Jeffrey “Ozzy” Otzwirk had a desire to serve the nation he loved so much. Leaving behind his home in Haugan, Montana in 1996, he served as a Machinist Mate in the US Navy. He served with country music star Jared Ashley on the USS Kitty Hawk, which had just returned from a second deployment to the Persian Gulf in 1998. Celebrating the ship’s return, the two went to a local bar just off base. It was the last time anyone would see Ozzy alive.",
